{{see|Patriot}}
==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[πατριώτης]]''' (''patriotes'') "of the same country", from '''[[πατρίς]]''' (''patris'') "father land, country", from '''[[πατήρ]]''' (''pater'') "father".

===Noun===
'''patriot'''
# A person who [[love]]s, [[support]]s, and [[defend]]s his or her [[country]], sometimes [[excessive]]ly.

